# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __getitem__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__getitem__')
#
# All 14 asyncio classes return false for __getitem__.
# asyncio types are concurrency primitives, not containers or mappings.
# No asyncio class exposes subscript access via [] in its own __dict__.
# StreamReader and StreamWriter handle byte streams, not indexed collections.
# asyncio.Queue, despite being a FIFO data structure, does not define
# __getitem__ — items are retrieved only via get() and get_nowait().
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

