# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __call__, __len__, __getitem__ across all 14 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 14 classes x 3 methods = 42 rows.
# __call__:    false for all 14 — asyncio objects use coroutine protocol, not callable.
# __len__:     false for all 14 — asyncio.Queue deliberately omits __len__ (use qsize()).
# __getitem__: false for all 14 — no asyncio type supports subscript access.
# This is the first wave in the asyncio campaign to yield all-false for all three
# methods across all 14 subjects simultaneously.
# Notable contrast with previous waves:
#   Wave 655 (as3121): TimerHandle true for __ge__; 12 classes true for __repr__.
#   Wave 656 (as3136): uniform false — asyncio types are pure concurrency primitives
#   with no callable, sized, or subscriptable protocol in their own __dict__.
# Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects (selected):
#   Wave 652 (as3076): __get__ — Task/Future/Queue/Handle true; others false.
#   Wave 653 (as3091): __eq__/__hash__ — several true; __bool__ — Semaphore/Lock true.
#   Wave 654 (as3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — TimerHandle true; others false.
#   Wave 655 (as3121): __ge__ — TimerHandle true; __repr__ — 12 classes true.
#   Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

